OL,3,C'Long over due, but they can't give us
OL,4,Cback the time we lost'
OL,6,FThe announcement that the government
OL,7,Fwill go ahead with a compensation
OL,8,Fscheme for victims of the contaminated
OL,9,Fblood scandal has received a 'cautious
OL,10,Fwelcome' from some of those affected.
OL,12,FIt comes after it was announced that
OL,13,Fvictims of the infected blood scandal
OL,14,Fwill receive support payments for life.
OL,16,FLabelled the "worst treatment disaster
OL,17,Fin the NHS," the infected blood
OL,18,Fscandal saw more than 30,000 people
OL,19,Finfected with HIV and Hepatitis C
OL,20,Fafter being treated with contaminated
OL,21,Fblood products.
